;; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
;; Integration: Worktrees
;; Launch-time snapshot of sibling Git worktree paths for cross-worktree read access.
;; Source: 50-integrations-core/worktrees.sb
;; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

;; Why this exists:
;; Multi-worktree flows often involve inspecting diffs, review branches, or
;; alternative implementations across sibling worktrees in the same repository.
;; Safehouse grants that visibility by default so agents can compare work
;; across existing worktrees without manual path flags.
;;
;; Limitations:
;; - The snapshot is computed once when Safehouse launches the wrapped process.
;; - New worktrees created after launch are NOT added to the running sandbox.
;; - Sibling worktrees stay read-only by default; use --add-dirs when you
;;   intentionally want broader write access to a stable worktree parent.
;;
;; Runtime snapshot (this placeholder comment line is replaced at launch):
;;   linked worktree read paths: __SAFEHOUSE_REPLACE_ME_WITH_GIT_LINKED_WORKTREE_PATHS_STATUS__
;;
;; Example generated rules (illustrative only; actual paths depend on launch):
;;   (allow file-read* (subpath "/Users/alice/src/project-review"))
;;   (allow file-read* (subpath "/Users/alice/src/project-fixup"))
;;
;; Runtime-generated rules are emitted immediately below this profile section.
